{{Infobox person |name = Ann Killion |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |death_cause = |resting_place = |resting_place_coordinates = |residence = [[Mill Valley, California]] |nationality = American |other_names = |known_for = |education = |alma_mater = |employer = |occupation = [[Sports journalism|Sports journalist]] |home_town = |title = |salary = |networth = |height = |weight = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |party = |boards = |religion = |spouse = |partner = |children = |parents = |relations = |signature = |website = http://annkillion.com/ |footnotes = }}
'''Ann Killion''' is an American sports journalist and author. She has written for [[Sports Illustrated]], [[San Francisco Chronicle]], [[Comcast Sportsnet]], [[San Jose Mercury News]], and [[The Los Angeles Times]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ann Killion|url=http://www.kcrw.com/people/ann-killion|publisher=KCRW|accessdate=14 January 2015}}</ref> She is the co-author of two books with Olympic gold medalists: ''Throw Like a Girl: How to Dream Big & Believe in Yourself'' with [[Jennie Finch]] and ''Solo: A Memoir of Hope'' with [[Hope Solo]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Almond|first1=Elliott|title=Bay Area author Ann Killion discusses upcoming Hope Solo book|url=http://blogs.mercurynews.com/olympics/2012/07/26/bay-area-author-ann-killion-discusses-upcoming-hope-solo-book/|publisher=San Jose Mercury News|accessdate=14 January 2015|date=July 26, 2012}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Killion was raised in [[Mill Valley, California]] and has two brothers, Paul and [[Tom Killion (artist)|Tom Killion]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marinmagazine.com/January-2015/9-Questions-for-Ann-Killion/|title=9 Questions for Ann Killion|last=|first=|date=2015-01-01|website=Marin Magazine|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-06-18}}</ref> She attended [[Tamalpais High School]] where she was the sports editor for the school newspaper.<ref name=marinmag_0115>{{cite web|last1=Hershon|first1=Marc|title=9 Questions for Ann Killion|url=http://www.marinmagazine.com/January-2015/9-Questions-for-Ann-Killion/|publisher=Marin Magazine|accessdate=14 January 2015|date=January 2015}}</ref> She completed her college degree at [[UCLA]] and obtained her Master's Degree in Journalism from [[Columbia University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About Ann Killion |url=http://annkillion.com/about/ |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090822091608/http://annkillion.com/about/ |dead-url=yes |archive-date=22 August 2009 |publisher=Ann Killion |accessdate=14 January 2015 }}</ref>
==Works== * ''Throw Like a Girl: How to Dream Big & Believe in Yourself.'' By [[Jennie Finch]] and Ann Killion. Location: 2011. * ''Solo: A Memoir of Hope.'' By [[Hope Solo]] and Ann Killion. Location: 2012.
