{{Infobox country at games | NOC = BLR | NOCname = | oldcode = | year = 2013 | date = | games = Summer Universiade | location = [[2013 Summer Universiade|Kazan]] | competitors = 163 | sports = | flagbearer = | officials = | gold = 13 | silver = 13 | bronze = 14 | rank = 5 | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | website = }}
'''[[Belarus]]''' competed at the [[2013 Summer Universiade]] in [[Kazan]], [[Russia]] from 6 July to 17 July 2013. 163 athletes are a part of the Belarusian team.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://kazan2013.ru/en/st_events/athletes#/hide/en/-240/Participant/List?isRelay=False&isAnimal=False&lastNameStarts=&sportId=&countryId=BLR |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-07-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130717101154/http://kazan2013.ru/en/st_events/athletes#/hide/en/-240/Participant/List?isRelay=False&isAnimal=False&lastNameStarts=&sportId=&countryId=BLR |archivedate=2013-07-17 |df= }}</ref>
Belarus won 40 medals (7th place), including 13 gold medals (5th place), more than United States.
