'''Floripa Esporte Clube''', also known as '''Super Imperatriz Vôlei''', was a men's [[volleyball]] team, based in [[Florianópolis]], [[Santa Catarina (state)|Santa Catarina]], [[Brazil]]. They won the [[Superliga Brasileira de Voleibol]] in 2005&ndash;06, 2007&ndash;08 and in 2008&ndash;09, and won the South American Championship in 2009. They played at [[Arena Jaraguá]]. The club was formerly known as '''Cimed Esporte Clube'''. The team was folded in July 2013 after finishing tenth in the 2012–13 [[Superliga Brasileira de Voleibol|Brazilian Superliga]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lancenet.com.br/minuto/Floripa-Esporte-Clube-disputar-Superliga_0_956304493.html|title=Floripa Esporte Clube não irá disputar a próxima Superliga de vôlei|language=Portuguese|publisher=Lance!Net|accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref>

==Titles==
* '''[[South American Men's Club Volleyball Championship|South American Championship]]:'''
** '''Winners (1):''' 2009
* '''[[Superliga Brasileira de Voleibol|Superliga]]:'''
** '''Winners (4):''' 2005&ndash;06, 2007&ndash;08, 2008&ndash;09, 2009&ndash;10
** '''Runners-up (1):''' 2006&ndash;07

