{{Infobox football club| clubname = Gangan FC| image = | fullname = Gangan Football Club| nickname = | founded = 1963 ''(as Sily Club de Kindia)''| ground = Stade de Kindia| capacity = 2,500| chairman = | manager = | league = [[Guinée Championnat National]]| season = 2013–14| position = Ligue 2, 1st ''(Promoted)''| }}
'''Gangan Football Club''' is a [[football club]] from [[Kindia]] in the [[West Africa]]n, state of [[Guinea]]. They play in the [[Guinée Championnat National]], which is the second highest league in Guinean football.
==History== In 1963 when the club was called '''Sily Club de Kindia''' the team has won the [[Guinée Coupe Nationale]].<ref>http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/guineacuphist.html</ref> The team was renamed Gangan Football Club in 2005.
