{{Infobox football biography | name = Gilbert Meriel | image = | image_size = 250 | caption = | fullname = Gilbert Meriel<ref>{{cite web|title=Squad lists for the FIFA Confederations Cup Brazil 2013|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/02/10/38/80/fcclop_neutral.pdf|publisher=Fédération Internationale de Football Association (FIFA)|accessdate=20 June 2013|format=PDF|date=7 June 2013}}</ref> | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|11|11|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Tahiti]] | height = {{height|m=1.86}} | position = [[Goalkeeper]] | currentclub = [[A.S. Vénus]] | clubnumber = 1 | youthyears1 = 1995–2000 | youthclubs1 = [[A.S. Vénus]] | youthyears2 = 2000–2003 | youthclubs2 = [[SCO Angers|Angers]] | youthyears3 = 2003–2006 | youthclubs3 = [[USJA Carquefou|Carquefou]] | years1 = 2006–2008 | clubs1 = [[USJA Carquefou|Carquefou]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2010–2011 | clubs2 = [[A.S. Tefana]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2011–2014 | clubs3 = [[AS Central Sport]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | clubs4 = [[A.S. Vénus]] | caps4 = | goals4 = | years4 = 2014– | nationalyears1 = 2012– | nationalteam1 = [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] | nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | club-update = | nationalteam-update = 20:16, 23 June 2013 (UTC) }}
'''Gilbert Meriel''' (born 11 November 1986) is a soccer player from [[Tahiti]] currently playing for [[A.S. Vénus]] and for the [[Tahiti national football team]]. He was part of the Tahitian squad at the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.gilbert.meriel.198743.en.html|title=Profile|date=|work=Football Database|accessdate=6 June 2013 }}</ref>
Meriel started playing soccer at the age of nine on Tahitian club [[A.S. Vénus]]. Five years later, he went to France to join the youth academy at [[Angers SCO]], where he stayed for three years. While in France, Meriel also played for [[US Jeanne d'Arc Carquefou]] competing in the lower leagues, before returning home at 18. Upon his return home Meriel, like many of his national team colleagues, was forced to get another job and become a [[semi-professional]] athlete. Metiel earned a bachelor in economy and administration, becoming an [[auditor]] for consulting group [[KPMG]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/players/player=360634/profile.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 17, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130618010234/http://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/players/player%3D360634/profile.html |archivedate=June 18, 2013 |df= }}</ref>
On the Confederations Cup, Meriel had his first [[cap (sports)|cap]] as the starting goalkeeper for Tahiti's in the squad's final game against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] in [[Recife]]. While Tahiti lost 8-0, Meriel was applauded once he saved a penalty kick from the eventually sent-off [[Andres Scotti]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/23022840 |title=Confederations Cup: Tahitian delight at penalty save |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=2013-06-23 |accessdate=2016-06-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=255199/match=300222465/summary.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=July 17, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130804205409/http://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round%3D255199/match%3D300222465/summary.html |archivedate=August 4, 2013 |df= }}</ref>
