{{infobox country at games | NOC = GUY | NOCname = Guyana Olympic Association | games = Olympics | year = | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 1 | officials = | appearances = | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = {{Team appearances list|team=Guyana|competition=Summer Olympics|begin_year=|end_year= }} | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Guyana]]''' has competed in 16 [[Summer Olympic Games]]. They have never competed in the Winter Games. For the first 5 games they appeared as [[British Guiana]]. The country has won a single medal, a bronze in boxing won by [[Michael Anthony (boxer)|Michael Anthony]] at the [[1980 Summer Olympics]].
The Guyana Olympic Association was created in 1935 and recognized by the [[International Olympic Committee]] in 1948.
