'''Little Falls Veterans Memorial Park''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Little Falls (city), New York|Little Falls, New York]]. It is primarily used for [[baseball]]. It is home to the [[Mohawk Valley DiamondDawgs]] of the [[Perfect Game Collegiate Baseball League]] and was the home of [[Little Falls Mets]]. The ballpark has a capacity of 2,000 people and opened in 1949.<ref>{{cite web|last=Swanson|first=Shawn|url=http://nycbl-sswanson-sswanson.blogspot.ca/|title=Diamondawgs History|date=19 February 2009|accessdate=16 December 2016}}</ref>
