[[Image:Stetson-bowl-stadium.jpg|thumb|Stetson Bowl stadium.]]
'''Stetson Bowl''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Surrey, British Columbia]], [[Canada]] built in 1948. Located in the [[Cloverdale Fairgrounds]], it was upgraded for minor league [[baseball]] and was the home field of the [[Surrey Glaciers]] of the [[Western Baseball League]] for the 1995 season. As a ballpark, the Stetson Bowl had a capacity of 5,000 people.<ref>[http://www.ballparkreviews.com/surrey/surrey.htm]</ref>

Today, it is the main venue of the [[Cloverdale Rodeo and Country Fair]]. "The Stetson Bowl Stadium is home to most of the Cloverdale Rodeo performances each year. Its total area is around {{convert|36400|sqft|m2|-1}} and its performance surface is made of sand. The bleachers can hold 4000 spectators and portable seating can accommodate 800 additional spectators. Besides the rodeo, the stadium is commonly used for filming, festivals, concerts, sporting events and dog training classes." <ref>[http://www.cloverdalerodeo.com/files/stetson-bowl.php Stetson Bowl at Cloverdale Rodeo<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

The Surrey school board was petitioned by a local trustee in 2008 who argued that the Stetson Bowl should be used for more than a livestock and showdog display area.  The petition seeks to transform The Stetson Bowl to more of a human sports stadium, so it could "be revitalized
and used more effectively for community and school sporting activities".<ref>[http://www.sd36.bc.ca/Board/meetings/0809/20080925stetsonbowl.pdf Surrey School district petitioned to investigate changes to Stetson bowl]</ref>

